<div id="pf8" class="pf w1 h16" data-page-no="8"><div class="pc pc8 w1 h16"><div class="t m102 x5b h1e ye0 ff5 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 1 </div><div class="t m103 x5e h1f ye1 ff2 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">*December 27â€”January 2 </div><div class="t m104 x55 h20 ye2 ff1 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Unique Purpose </div><div class="t m105 x55 h20 ye3 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of </div><div class="t m106 x5f h21 ye4 ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John&apos;s Gospel </div><div class="t m107 x55 h7 y6c ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH AFTERNOON </div><div class="t m108 x60 h22 ye5 ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read for This Week&apos;s Study: </div><div class="t m19 x40 h2 ye6 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> Luke 1:1-4, John 15:1-8, </div><div class="t m109 x55 h2 ye7 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17:20, 20:24-31, 21:20-25. </div><div class="t m10a x60 h22 ye8 ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Memory Text: </div><div class="t m10b x23 h7 ye9 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> &quot;Then Jesus told him, &apos;Because you have seen </div><div class="t m10c x55 h7 yea ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">me, you have believed; blessed are those who have not seen and yet </div><div class="t m69 x55 h7 yeb ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">have believed&apos; &quot; </div><div class="t m10d x61 h2 yec ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 20:29, NIV). </div><div class="t m10e x60 h22 yed ff3 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Key Thought: </div><div class="t m10f x61 h7 y47 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> The Gospel of John tells us that the absence of </div><div class="t m110 x62 h7 yee ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">physical contact with Jesus is no disadvantage to those seeking a </div><div class="t m111 x62 h7 yef ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">relationship with Him today. Jesus&apos; word is as powerful as His </div><div class="t m39 x62 h7 yf0 ff5 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">touch. </div><div class="t m112 x62 h23 yf1 ff5 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">H</div><div class="t m42 x5c h2 yf2 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ave you ever wished you could have known Jesus in the flesh, </div><div class="t m113 x5c h2 yf3 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as His disciples did? Have you ever wished He lived at your </div><div class="t m114 x5c h2 yf4 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">house? Wouldn&apos;t it be great to take your problems directly to </div><div class="t m115 x62 h2 y4d ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him, face to face? To go to Him and share what&apos;s on your heart and </div><div class="t m112 x62 h2 yf5 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then see Him go to His knees and pray earnestly to His Father for you? </div><div class="t m116 x62 h2 y90 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Wouldn&apos;t it be easier to have a relationship with Jesus if He lived, </div><div class="t m117 x62 h2 yf6 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">breathed, walked, and talked at your house? </div><div class="t m118 x19 h2 yf7 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">But that privilege has not been ours. Yet, the good news is that the </div><div class="t m119 x62 h2 yf8 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gospel of John helps assure us that we don&apos;t need physical contact with </div><div class="t m11a x62 h2 yf9 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus in order to have a relationship with Him. We don&apos;t need physical </div><div class="t m11b x62 h2 yfa ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">contact to obtain all the blessings He is willing and able to give. John </div><div class="t m11c x62 h2 yfb ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">even recalls Jesus telling His disciples &quot; &apos;It is for your good that I am </div><div class="t m11d x62 h2 yfc ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">going away&apos; &quot; </div><div class="t m11e x63 h2 yfc ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 16:7, NIV). </div><div class="t m11f x58 h2 yfc ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Through the presence of the Spirit, the </div><div class="t m120 x62 h2 yfd ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">work of Jesus is enhanced by His absence </div><div class="t m121 x38 h2 yfd ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(John 14:12). </div><div class="t m122 x19 h2 yfe ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This week we take our first look at this good news. </div><div class="t 